  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Recent advances in LLM-based multi-agent systems (MAS) significantly enhance performance across various industries, such as multi-agent pathfinding (Chen, Koenig, and Dilkina 2025), multi-turn negotiation (Dong 2024), and multirobotics cooperation (RoCo) (Mandi, Jain, and Song 2024; Wang et al. 2025a).",
    "In these tasks, LLMs have demonstrated capabilities in high-level planning and task decomposition, making them promising for intricate multi-agent cooperation.",
    "However, existing LLM-based MAS benchmarks (Wu et al. 2023; Chen et al. 2024) mainly rely on predefined characters or fixed cooperative pipelines, leveraging fixed dialogue sequences and characterized prompting engineering to enhance the performance of LLM.",
    "It remains unclear how LLMs can coordinate and self-organize with other agents in long-term tasks, limiting the evaluation of their autonomy.",
    "Meanwhile, the tool usage of LLM offers a natural entry point for evaluating LLM cooperation and self-organization abilities."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
